Full Title: 2nd International ELT Conference 

Date: 07-May-2010 - 08-May-2010
Location: Istanbul, Turkey 
Contact Person: Y?ld?ray Cevik
Meeting Email: elt@maltepe.edu.tr
Web Site: http://elted.maltepe.edu.tr 

Linguistic Field(s): Applied Linguistics; Ling & Literature; Sociolinguistics 

Subject Language(s): English (eng)

Call Deadline: <deadline>15-Jan-2010</deadline> 

Meeting Description:

We would like to invite you to our 2nd International ELT Conference which will
be held on May 7-8, 2010 in Istanbul, hosted by Maltepe University, Department
of English Language Teaching. 

Call for Papers

Topics of interest include but not limited to: 
- Teacher training and teacher development 
- ELF and Language Teaching
- Second language acquisition and learning  
- Cultural studies and ELT 
- Approaches and methods  
- Teaching and Learning technologies  
- Testing, evaluation and assessment  
- Critical ELT 
- Corpus linguistics and English language teaching  
- Curriculum and syllabus design and planning 
- The teaching of the four skills  
- The teaching of grammar  
- The teaching of vocabulary  
- ESP teaching and learning
- ELT management
- Translation and English language teaching  
- Teaching English to young learners  
- Materials design and production  
- Literature and English Language Teaching
- Language teacher cognition
- Language teachers' conceptions of research
- Multilingualism and Interculturalism
- Non-native English speaking teachers

Our plenary speakers will be: 
Prof. Dr. Ay?e Akyel, Yeditepe University
Prof. Dr. Cem Alptekin, Bosphorus University
Prof. Dr. Simon Borg, University of Leeds
Prof Dr. Enric Llurda, Universitat de Lleida

The deadline for proposals will be <deadline>January 15th, 2010</deadline>. The abstracts for papers
should not exceed 400 words (min. 250), for workshops and panel discussions 700
words (min. 500). They should have up to 5 main references. Proposals will be
considered by the referee committee who will decide on the acceptance or refusal
of the contribution. We aim to let you know whether your proposal has been
accepted or refused by the beginning of March 2010.

Please direct any inquiries and your proposals to the conference e-mail address:
elt@maltepe.edu.tr    

You may also visit http://elted.maltepe.edu.tr. for further and updated
information about the Conference. 

We are looking forward to seeing you in Istanbul! 

Assoc.Prof.Dr. Firdevs Karahan
fkarahan@maltepe.edu.tr





